    'month' => '08',
    'index' => 'an108',
    'body' => 'I just got my copy of Star Vikings yesterday, and I wanted to give a
quick and general review of it.

The book is priced at $13.00 and is 93 pages in length. 
1. Cover Art: Ok cover art. Not bad, but not remarkable either.

2. Interior Arts & Text: The book describes 32 NPCS, divided into 4
catogories of 8 NPC.
 -Coalition Officals: People who are the movers and shakers of
 the coalition.
 -Ship Captains: 8 description of different ship captians
 -Coalition Personnel: People in the Coalition that the do the
 day to day work in the coalition. Describe as people the PCs would
 probably encouter.
 -Outsiders: Non Coalition NPCS that can be introduced in a
 campaign. This sections Includes a couple TEDS, a hiver, and a
 Ithklur Marine.

The NPC description is about a page in length which include name, age
(in 1201), attributes, background, career path, assets, appearance,
personality, motivation, how to referee the NPC, and quotation. There
is also a full page picture with each NPC.

The book also included ship stats for 6 different ship, with the
modification made by the owner/captain.

3. Color Section: The middle section is once again in color. The pages
show color pictures of the different ships, and color sector maps of
the Thoezennt, Promise, Shenk, Khulam sub-sectors. The map include the
trade routes for different ships.

4 Likes & Dislikes: Over all it is a well done source book. The book
is well organized, and well thought out. The problems I have is that
the border arts is again too large on some pages (minor nitpick), and
that The don\'t like have color pages in the middle of the supplement.
I know from the past, when I get a gaming book with color pages in the
middle, they tend to fall out with-in 3-5 years.

I would suggest GMs to look at it, and see if it would be useful in
your campaign. It would probably only be useful for TNE GMs the run a
Coalition campaign.

mike

-- 
