> The following list is derived from one I created in a pretty but 
> non-accessible format (interleaf).  It is not as extensive as the list 
> posted a few days ago, but it includes more detail on the races it lists.
> 
> For each race, it includes the home planet location, a thumbnail sketch,
and
> where to look for more data. I will add the additional listings from the 
> other list with the matyerial from bun108 (if the archives come back) and 
> repost the expanded list.
> 
> Feel free to mail me corrections (slings and arrows etc).
> 
> Note for you TNEers (tin ears): most of these races live on at least one 
> world they would easily have survived upon, so odds are they are still 
> around.  However, the "domain ruled" information will be off.
> 
>       enjoy,
>       Ted7
> 
> 
> The list is divided into Major races, Minor races, Minor Human Races:
> 
> Race            Home World
> 
> Droyne          Unknown;
>                 probably in Spinward Marches
> 
> The Droyne are the survivors of the Ancients.   They are a multi-part race;
> an individual "castes"  to become a member of a subspecies suited to a
> particular role.  Uncasted members do not fully  develop and live as
> chirpers.  The Droyne are  psionically inclined.  See "Aliens 6: Droyne."
> 
> 
> Fteirle         Kusyu / Dark Nebula 1919
> (Aslan)
> 
> Evolved from carnivorous hunters, they developed  a society structured by
> clan; no central government. Culture places great value on honor to balance
> natural aggression. Their society spans 17  sectors spinward of Solomani
> space. See "Aslan &  Solomani."
> 
> 
> Hivers          (planet) / Ricenden I (Guaran)
> 
> Developed from beings that look like star fish.   They are good with
> computers.  They prefer subtle  manipulation to confrontation or overt
> action.   They control a several sector domain Trailing of  the Solomani
> Confederation. "See Aliens 7: Hivers."
> 
> 
> K\'kree          Kirur / Ruupiin F (Thirty)
> (Centaurs)
> 
> The K\'kree developed from hexapodal herd animals, developing intelligence
> for defense. They  have a several sector realm trailing the Vargr Extents
> and the 3rd Imperium.  See "Aliens 2: K\'kree".
> 
> 
> Solomani                Terra / Solomani Rim 1827
> (Humaniti major)
> 
> The Solomani humans come from humaniti\'s original home: Terra.  Solomani
> are known for their  curiosity, impetuosity, and belief that they should
> rule scattered humaniti.  The Solomani Confederation is an 8 sector domain
> rimward of of Imperial  space.  See "Aslan & Solomani."
> 
> 
> Vargr                   Lair / Provence 2402
> 
> Geneered by the Ancients 300K years ago from  terran canines.  Their mental
> capacity was uplifted  to sentience and their fore paws were reformed as
> hands.  They are spread over 18 sectors with no  encompassing government
> coreward of Imperial  space.  See "Vilani & Vargr."
> 
> 
> Vilani                  Vland / Vland 1717
> (Humaniti major)
> 
> Taken from Terra 300K years ago by Ancients;   developed jump drive and
> created the 28-sector  First Empire, which lasted a few K years before
> falling within 2 centuries of meeting the Solomani.  Pure-stock Vilani
> known for long life span (up to  200 years).  Culture is group-oriented,
> known for  careful, deliberate planning. See "Vilani & Vargr."
> 
> 
> Zhodani                 Zdhant / Zhdant
> (Humaniti major)
> 
> Taken from earth 300K years ago by Ancients;  developed a psionically-
> oriented society now  dominating a several-sector domain spinward of Vargr
> space that eventually came in conflict with the 3rd Imperium. See "Aliens
> 4: Zhodani."
> 
> 
> 
> Minor Alien Races
> 
> Race                    Home world
> 
> Adduxar                 Addux? / Tienspevnekr G
> 
> Carnivorous reptilian race with small stellar empire of about 37 planets
> met peacefully by the  Zhodani as they expanded.  Currently Zhodani
> citizens with a 10 planet reservation. See Aliens 4: Zhodani.
> 
> 
> Ael Jael                Jaelayla / "Coreward edge of the  Imperium"
