From: christop@ifi.uio.no (Christopher Henrik Lund)
Newsgroups: rec.games.design
Subject: Movement rates of animals
Date: 27 Sep 1994 10:18:17 +0100
Organization: Dept. of Informatics, University of Oslo, Norway
Keywords: Animals
 
 
My original request for movement rates got me >lots< of stuff on humans and
horses (thank you), and also a few comments on oxen, but nothing on the
various other animals. So here\'s what I found in the library:
 
 
        MOVEMENT RATES OF VARIOUS ANIMALS
 
I dug this up in the library. The numbers are probably inaccurate, since it is 
hard to clock a wild animal (they don\'t always want to cooperate). The figures 
are in kilometers per hour.
 
MAMMALS
 
Moose ("Elg")           56      short distances only
Reindeer                51      short distances only
Deer                    40-67   average-max
Horse                   60      short distances
Cheetah                 96-100  short distances only
Wolf                    6-10    normal rate
                        55-65   short distances
Dog                     69      max
Hare                    outruns a wolf
Fox                     42      average max
Seal                    35-65   average-max
Killer Whale            64      short distances
Blue Whale              37      10-15 minutes
Antilope                50-67, up to ~80
 
BIRDS
 
Geese                   40-120  migratory speed
Ducks                   60-113  migratory speed
Eagle                   45-190  average-dive
Falcon                  40-300  average-dive
Diverse waders          50-70   migratory speed
Seagull                 ~50     average
Pigeons                 50-90   migratory speed
Pigeon, carrier         90-95   average
Owl                     65-70   pressed
Raven/crow              ~50     migratory speed
Swallow                 45-60   migratory speed
Diverse small birds     30-50   migratory speed
 
FISH
 
Blue shark              69      max
Salmon                  13      average
                        43      max
Trout                   9       average
Mackerel                11-33   average-max
Sturgeon                70-104(?)       average-max
Swordfish               64      max
Sailfish                110     max
 
 
Hope this is of some use to somebody. It would be interesting to have some
figures on the movement rates of various insects, arachnids, reptiles, and
amphibians as well.
 
                                        C Lund,
                                        Oslo    
